From b1e401959499784a4280d2f8d50581050a89a3ea Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sri Vidya Gunturi <sgunturi@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Jun 2025 11:05:55 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 06/20] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Add hostapd config to input
 EPCS params

Add config support to input EPCS_WMM and EPCS_MUEDCA params. Extract these
parameters from the hostapd config settings and add them as part of the
Priority Access Multi-Link element in the EPCS Request and EPCS Response action
frames for the below explained scenarios-

AP MLD adds these params to Priority Access Multi-Link elemet and sends in the
EPCS Request Action frame to the non-AP MLD.

If the non-AP MLD sends a EPCS Request frame to AP MLD. Then AP MLD adds these
params to the Priority Access Multi-Link elemet and sends in the EPCS Response
action frame to the non-AP MLD.

Set default values for these params if the user did not configure.

Signed-off-by: Sri Vidya Gunturi <sgunturi@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 hostapd/config_file.c | 153 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 hostapd/hostapd.conf  |  52 ++++++++++++++
 src/ap/ap_config.c    |  44 ++++++++++++
 src/ap/ap_config.h    |   6 ++
 4 files changed, 255 insertions(+)

